  "texts": [
    "Following this, to measure the accuracy we take the intersection over union (IoU) of a ground truth bounding box and the estimated box to determine how close to the correct bounding box the prediction is.",
    "This provides a loss function to use during model optimization (Bandyopadhyay 2022).",
    "Several versions of YOLO have been used in IC applications, the current variant being YOLOv8 (Jocher et al. 2023), which was used in KTU (2024) for detecting and segmenting distractors for soccer games.",
    "Ov2 supports the prediction of a fixed number objects in a single block, resulting in improved detection of smaller and grouped objects.",
    "Ov3 builds on this by introducing a model (with higher complexity) that can detect smaller objects and preserve fine detail."
  ],
